<h3>What is the difference between formatting and minification?</h3>

<p>Formatting (also called beautifying or pretty-printing) adds whitespace, indentation, and line breaks to make code human-readable. Minification does the opposite: it removes all unnecessary whitespace, shortens variable names, and strips comments to produce the smallest possible file size. Both are important — formatting for development and minification for production.</p>

